The '''angelic being''' is a [[monster class]] that appears in ''[[NetHack]]'', and is represented by the uppercase [[A]] glyph ({{white|A}}). Angelic beings are designated internally by the macro '''S_ANGEL'''.{{refsrc|include/monsym.h|41|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}

The monster class contains the following [[monster]]s:{{refsrc|src/monst.c|985|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}

* {{monsymlink|couatl}}
* {{monsymlink|Aleax}}
* {{monsymlink|Angel}}
* {{monsymlink|ki-rin}}
* {{monsymlink|Archon}}

==Common traits==
All angelic beings are lawful with the exception of Angels: though an Angel's default alignment is lawful, Angels that serve as the [[minion]] of a [[god]] will have the same alignment as that god.

Angelic beings are [[strong]] and [[inediate]] monsters that are considered [[M2_NASTY|nasty]], have [[infravision]], can be seen with infravision, and can [[follow]] the [[hero]] to other levels if they are adjacent. Angelic beings can [[fly]] with the exception of the Aleax, and can all [[see invisible]] except for the couatl. Angelic beings ignore the effects of [[Elbereth]] as well as occupied [[sanctuary]].

Except for the ki-rin, angelic beings possess [[poison resistance]].

{{upcoming|3.7.0|Ki-rin also possess poison resistance.}}

===Generation===
Randomly-generated angelic beings are likely to be created peaceful towards [[lawful]] characters that have good [[alignment record]], with the exception of Angels: Angels that serve the same god as the hero, or else are "renegade" servants of other gods are likely to be peaceful if the hero has good alignment record; Angels that serve different gods from the hero or are "renegade" servants of the hero's god will always be hostile. Angelic beings will never be generated randomly in [[Gehennom]].

[[Humanoid]] angelic beings are [[Monster starting inventory|generated with]] an uncursed [[erodeproof]] +0 [[large shield]] {{frac|3|4}} of the time, and an uncursed +0 [[shield of reflection]] otherwise, and their weapon will be a blessed erodeproof [[long sword]] of an enchantment from +0 to +3, with a {{frac|5}} chance of the sword being made into either [[Demonbane]] or [[Sunsword]] if neither artifact has been generated.{{refsrc|src/makemon.c|326|nethack=3.6.7}} A humanoid angelic being that is a [[M2_LORD|lord]] to their kind, i.e. an Archon, will always generate with a shield of reflection, and their long sword will always be made into an artifact if possible.

Angelic beings [[Corpseless|do not leave a corpse]] upon death.

{{upcoming|3.7.0|Demonbane's base item is changed to a [[mace]], so no angelic being can generate with it.}}

==History==
Angelic beings are all introduced in [[NetHack 3.1.0]].

==Variants==
===SLASH'EM===
[[SLASH'EM]] adds some new angelic beings to the monster class:

* {{monsymlink|movanic deva}}
* {{monsymlink|monadic deva}}
* {{monsymlink|astral deva}}
* {{monsymlink|Planetar}}
* {{monsymlink|Solar}}

Angelic beings other than the couatl and Aleax possess [[death resistance]], and all angelic beings [[Need +x weapon to hit|need a weapon of a certain enchantment to be hit]], while [[Hits creatures as +x weapon|hitting as weapons of that same enchantment]]. Planetars and Solars are considered lords to their kind.

Tame angelic beings can be gifted as minions to lawful characters via [[sacrifice]] or [[prayer]], except for Angels and Aleaxes.

===UnNetHack===
[[UnNetHack]] adds some new angelic beings to the monster class:

* {{monsymlink|Dark Angel}}
